use strict;
use vars qw($VERSION);
$VERSION='0.022';
use FindBin qw($Bin);
my ($handler)=($0=~/docbook2(\w+)$/);
exec "$Bin/docbook-convert", "--handler=$handler", @ARGV

__END__


=pod

=head1 docbook2pod(5)

=head1 NAME

docbook2pod - Convert Docbook articles and refentry pages to Perl
    POD

=head1 SYNOPSIS

C<<<< docbook2pod file.xml >>>>

=head1 Description

docbook2pod is an alias for the  C<<<< docbook-convert >>>>  utility pre-configured to produce POD output (i.e. Identical to using C<<<< docbook-convert --pod >>>> ). See the C<<<< docbook-convert >>>>  man page for the full option list.

=cut